values: 杂志；期刊；弹匣；弹仓；弹盘；弹夹；弹药箱；军火库；弹药库；军械库；储藏室；仓库；胶卷盒；（电视、广播）专题节目

word_mean_info__list.difference: 本义为“日报”，现在可指定期发生的周刊、月刊、季刊等或指学术团体出版的刊物、杂志或学报。
指刊登各种文章、小说、诗歌、评议的杂志。
系报刊总称，也指报界或报业。
通常指除日报以外的定期出版刊物。
多指登载评论性文章或讨论重大事件的文章的刊物。
一般指每日出版的报纸。

word_group.brief_definition: 时尚杂志；时装杂志；时尚周刊
杂志文章；报刊文章；杂志上的文章
商业杂志；商务杂志；商业类杂志
通俗杂志；非学术性刊物
服装杂志（含很多图片）；画报

bilingual.target: 他读了一本新的电影杂志。

bilingual.source: But we can give away the magazine.
bilingual.target: 但我们可以送掉这本杂志。

bilingual.source: I want to buy the new film magazine.
bilingual.target: 我想买那本新的电影杂志。

bilingual.source: The magazine is new but it's boring.
bilingual.target: 这本杂志是新的，但很无聊。

bilingual.source: You can read an article in a magazine.
bilingual.target: 你可以在杂志上读到一篇文章。

bilingual.source: Imagine you are designing a new magazine.
bilingual.target: 想象一下你在设计一本新杂志。

bilingual.source: I read a great article in my magazine.
bilingual.target: 我在我的杂志上读了一篇很棒的文章。

bilingual.source: The magazine ‘Cars' might not be about fishing.
bilingual.target: 《汽车》杂志可能不是关于钓鱼的。

bilingual.source: Jaber saw the advert for this job in a magazine.
bilingual.target: 贾贝尔在杂志上看到了这个工作的广告。

list.abstract: “Magazine”(“期刊”或“杂志”)一词源自法文Magasin，原义为“仓库”、“知识的仓库”或“军用品供应库”等。“Journal”一词在西文中也常等同于中文的期刊或杂志，创刊于1665年1月5日的《博学者杂志》(Journal des Scavans)即采用Journal一词，这在法文和英文中并无区别。在中文里，Journal有时被译为或对应以“学报”(Learned Journal)，但其本义仍为期刊或杂志。

yingyinNormal.en: Jordan, you look great! You're in a huge magazine.
yingyinNormal.zh: Jordan，你看起来可帅了，你上了知名杂志。

yingyinNormal.en: You think this is just a magazine. Hmm? This is not just a magazine.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你以为这只是本杂志，对吗？这不仅仅是杂志。

yingyinNormal.en: There was a magazine in the ladies' waiting room at King's Cross.
yingyinNormal.zh: 国王十字车站的女士候车室里有份杂志。

yingyinNormal.en: You're reading a magazine. You come across a full-page nude photo of a girl.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你可以在杂志里看到都是女性裸体的图片。

yingyinNormal.en: And it's such a great one that I just want to show you the cover of the magazine.
yingyinNormal.zh: 那么大，我很想给你们看看杂志的封面。

yingyinNormal.en: Hey, your copy of Science Magazine was in my mailbox. Oh, thanks. Mm-hmm.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你的《科学》杂志寄到了我的邮箱里。哦，谢了。

yingyinNormal.en: Here's a nice magazine. Thank you, Peppa. And here's some pretty music.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这里有好看的杂志。谢谢你，佩奇。这里还有好听的音乐。

yingyinNormal.en: Sounds as if he hates running a magazine. He hates me. Let's leave it at that.
yingyinNormal.zh: 听起来他很不喜欢办杂志啊。说白了就是他讨厌我。

yingyinNormal.en: Bloomberg says on the cover of the magazine: Yes, the Chinese army is spying on you.
yingyinNormal.zh: 彭博社在杂志封面上说：是的，中国军队在侦查你。

yingyinNormal.en: What are you guys talking about? There's a reception for my magazine article on Saturday.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你们在说什么？周六有场为我的杂志文章举行的招待会。

yingyinNormal.en: People magazine is having a reception this Saturday and I managed to get you invited.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这周六《人物》杂志要举行个招待会，我设法让你们也被邀请了。

yingyinNormal.en: Any of the other choices would have found that job impossible and the magazine would have suffered.
yingyinNormal.zh: 任何其他人选都无法胜任这项工作杂志社自身也会受影响。

yingyinNormal.en: So I think that if we get these samples into the magazine by Monday, we're gonna be fine. Sounds good.
yingyinNormal.zh: 周一前把样品交给杂志社，应该就没问题了。听起来不错。

yingyinNormal.en: Here's a nice magazine. Thank you, Peppa. And here's some pretty music. Thank you, Peppa.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这里有好看的杂志。谢谢你，佩琪。这里还有好听的音乐。谢谢你佩琪。

yingyinNormal.en: Oh, show them one of your hats, Romes. The purple one Pippa Middleton wore in Star Magazine.
yingyinNormal.zh: 罗米，给她们看一顶你的帽子，就是八卦杂志上那位社交名媛戴着的紫帽子。

yingyinNormal.en: There's no point in shouting at me, Mr Skinner. I want what you want: a magazine people like to read.
yingyinNormal.zh: 没必要对我大呼小叫的，斯金纳先生，我们都想办一本人人爱看的杂志。

yingyinNormal.en: Okay, here. What actor holds the record for being named people magazine's sexiest man alive? William Shatner.
yingyinNormal.zh: 好吧，这个哪位演员被"人物"杂志评为当前最性感男人？威廉·夏纳。

yingyinNormal.en: Now let's look at where we are in reality, recent headlines, in the media, include Foreign Policy magazine.
yingyinNormal.zh: 那现在来看看，现实中我们的情况，媒体中最近的标题，包括外交政策杂志。

yingyinNormal.en: You're going to go down swinging, huh? All right, well, we got your body lotion, your InStyle Magazine, your jewelry box.
yingyinNormal.zh: 还不承认嘛？好吧，看看你的护肤乳液，你的瑞丽杂志，你的首饰盒。

yingyinNormal.en: I could also be the engineer who builds the crossbow that kills Sheldon. You still might get on a magazine.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我也可以成为那个造出一把弩弓用来射杀谢尔顿的工程师。你仍然可能因此上杂志。

direction_info.description:
数据源自2012-2023年12年间全国考研试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2012-2023年全国考研英语一和考研英语二共24套考研试卷，包括阅读、完型填空、翻译、写作等所有题型。

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>
精选全国考研考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2012-2023年12年间全国考研英语一和考研英语二试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

examination_example.sentence: The first published sketch, "A Dinner at Poplar Walk" brought tears to Dickens's eyes when he discovered it in the pages of The Monthly <highlight>Magazine</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 当狄更斯发现他的第一部短篇小说《白杨庄晚宴》在《月刊》上发表时，他热泪盈眶。

examination_example.sentence: At the same time, Dickens, who had a reporter's eye for transcribing the life around him, especially anything comic or odd, submitted short sketches to obscure <highlight>magazines</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 同时，狄更斯以记者的眼光来记录他周围的生活，特别是任何滑稽或奇怪的事情，他向不知名的杂志提交了短篇素描。

disambiguation_list.sense_disambiguation: 一般指大开本，有插图的杂志，内有小说、广告、诗歌、问题的讨论等，定期出版发行。
尤其指对过去所发生事件进行陈述说明的杂志或日报，一般都有主要的对象和专题。
指一切定期出版的学术期刊。

examination_example.sentence: But it's so much more than the reductive depictions we see in women's <highlight>magazines</highlight> and on the Hollywood big screen.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 但它比我们在女性杂志和好莱坞大银幕上看到的简化描写要多得多。

examination_example.sentence: If the only reading you ever do is the novel or <highlight>magazine</highlight>, the speed at which you read-probably does not matter very much.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 如果你唯一的阅读量就是看小说和杂志，那么阅读速度就不那么重要了。

examination_example.sentence: There are a few sports <highlight>magazines</highlight> on the table.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 桌子上有几本体育杂志。

examination_example.sentence: Around me in this picture are the things that were very important in my life at that time: car <highlight>magazines</highlight> and musical instruments.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在这张照片中，我的周围是我当时生活中非常重要的事情：汽车杂志和乐器。
